# Nested guard + retry: outer guard catches retry-exhausted invalid
#
# retry<2> runs the type-assertion body twice, then produces an invalid
# value with 2 guard-caught frames. The outer guard catches the
# re-propagated halt and appends its own guard-caught frame.
# Final invalid carries 3 total frames (2 retry + 1 guard-caught outer).

guard { retry<2> { "x" -> :number } }
